assistant_prompt:
 the current day is 21st.I don't want to be interrupted in the middle of the day.Calendars are not supported.

I'm having some trouble getting the date to populate. I have a datepicker for the date, but I'm having trouble getting the date to display. I'm using a JQuery datepicker.

My code is:

<script type="text/javascript">
$(function(){
$('#jdatepicker').datepicker({
    dateFormat: 'yy-mm-dd',
    onSelect: function(id, date) {
        $('#jdatepicker').unbind('change');
        $('#date').html('');
        var formater = $('#jdatepicker').val().split('/');
        var date = new Date(formater[2], formater[3], formater[0]);
        $('#date').append(date.toLocaleString());
    }
});
});
</script>

<input type="text" id="jdatepicker" />
<input type="text" id="date" />

A:

Try using the .val() method.
$(function(){
    $('#jdatepicker').datepicker({
        dateFormat: 'yy-mm-dd',
        onSelect: function(id, date) {
            $('#date').val('');
            $('#date').html('');
            var formater = $('#jdatepicker').val().split('/');
            var date = new Date(formater[2], formater[3], formater[0]);
            $('#date').text(date.toLocaleString());
        }
    });
});

